        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:34PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Almyra, or near Stuttgart, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Stuttgart...                      Holly Grove...
Humphrey...                       Almyra...
St. Charles...                    Ulm...
Aberdeen...                       Almyra Airport...
Casscoe...                        Crocketts Bluff...
Ragtown...                        Indian Bay...
Pine City...                      Lawrenceville...
Cross Roads in Monroe County...   Bayou Meteo State Game Area...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
